transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Yes sir, I have been being charged on my Discover card for Score Blue and I'm not receiving—

Speaker 2: Them, and somebody has done it in my name that I did not get permission to do, and I need—

Speaker 1: To cancel that order ship. What is your first and last name?

Speaker 2: Royce, R-O-Y-C-E, Fouse, F-O-U-S-E.

Speaker 1: What's your phone number?

Speaker 2: I got a cell of 903-517-5455 and I'm calling you on my home—

Speaker 1: Number of 903-485-4302. Alright, so which one do you have on file with this? Was it—

Speaker 2: The cell phone or the home phone?

Speaker 1: Probably the cell. Okay, give it to me one more time.

Speaker 2: 903-517-5455.

Speaker 1: Okay. Alright sir, this is your VIP customer here with us getting a Viagra.

Speaker 2: Do you mind if I ask why you're cancelling or you said that you didn't order it?

Speaker 1: All I did was order it and I never received it. Are you at 1129 Industrial Drive?

Speaker 2: No. What about the 3265 County Road?

Speaker 1: That's my home.

Speaker 2: What's the Industrial Drive address?

Speaker 1: That's a business in town.

Speaker 2: Yeah, it looks like it was shipped to that address.

Speaker 1: Yeah, that's a business in town. I used to work there a long time ago, but I haven't in a long time.

Speaker 2: Somebody used that address.

Speaker 1: Okay, yeah, that's weird.

Speaker 2: Yeah, my Walmart account had been hacked.

Speaker 1: Amazon and eBay and a couple of credit cards.

Speaker 2: So you don't need this medication you're saying?

Speaker 1: Yeah, I don't.

Speaker 2: No, you can order this as needed. You don't have to worry about it.

Speaker 1: Yeah, my wife had cancer for eight years, so I haven't needed it or nothing, so.

Speaker 2: Okay, sir, we'll take care of it.

Speaker 1: Okay, can I get an email saying it has been or a text or something?

Speaker 2: We just have the verbal confirmation. We don't really send an email for that, but your prescription—

Speaker 1: Is cancelled. You will never receive this again.

Speaker 2: Is there any way I can receive any credits on any of it? I've looked at it four times.

Speaker 1: It's a 90-day return policy that we have, so all that would be outside of the return policy.

Speaker 2: Okay, all right, I appreciate it.

Speaker 1: You're welcome.

Speaker 2: Okay, bye.
